> "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Lie" (2) -> 0]
> "\"It's a lonely life in this place,\" I reply. \"Lonely - and still one never gets a moment to oneself.\"\n" [Continue]
