> "He nods. He has brought two cups of tea in metal mugs: he sets them down on the tabletop between us.\n" [Choices: "Take one" (0), "\"What's going on?\"" (1), "Wait" (2) -> 0]
> "I take a mug and warm my hands. It's a small gesture of friendship.\n" [Continue]
> "Enough to give me hope?\n" [Choices: "Drink" (0), "Wait" (1) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "I raise the cup to my mouth but it's too hot to drink.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Quite a difficult situation,\" Harris begins, sternly. I've seen him adopt this stiff tone of voice before, but only when talking to the brass. \"I'm sure you agree.\"\n" [Choices: "Agree" (0), "Disagree" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"Awkward,\" I reply\n" [Choices: "The stolen component..." (0), "Shrug" (1) -> 0]
> "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n" [Continue]
> "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n" [Choices: "Panic" (0), "Calculate" (1), "Deny" (2) -> 0]
> "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he replies, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 0]
> "\"I do.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris stares back at me. He cannot have expected it to be so easy to break me.\n" [Continue]
> "\"I see.\"\n" [Continue]
> "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n" [Continue]
> "\"You want to explain that?\"\n" [Choices: "Explain" (0), "Don't explain" (1), "Lie" (2), "Evade" (3) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "I pause a moment, trying to choose my words. To just come out and say it, after a lifetime of hiding... that is a circle I cannot square.\n" [Choices: "Explain" (0), "Lie" (1) -> 0]
> "\"I've done things,\" I begin. \"Things I didn't want to do. I tried not to. But in the end, it felt like cutting off my own arm to resist.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n" [Choices: "Yes" (0), "No" (1), "Evade" (2) -> 1]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"I'm not saying anything of the sort,\" I snap back. \"What is this, Harris? You're accusing me of treachery but I don't see a shred of evidence for it! Why don't you put your cards on the table?\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"It's simple enough,\" Harris says. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n" [Continue]
> "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Now they own you.\"\n" [Choices: "Agree" (0), "Disagree" (1), "Lie" (2) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"What could I do?\" I'm shaking now. The night is cold and the heat—lamp in the Hut has been removed. \"I don't want to go to prison.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"Smart man,\" he replies. \"You wouldn't last.  So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n" [Continue]
> "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n" [Choices: "Confess" (0), "Dissemble" (1) -> 1]
> "\"I saw Hooper take it.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"I see.\" He is starting to lose his patience. I have seen Harris angry a few times, with lackeys and secretaries. But never with us. With the 'brains' he has always been cautious, treating us like children.\n" [Continue]
> "And now I see that, like a father, he wants to smack us when we disobey him.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Just get to the truth, man. Every <i>minute</i> matters.\"\n" [Choices: "Tell the truth" (0), "Persist with this" (1) -> 1]
> "\"This is the truth.\"\n" [Continue]
> "I have become, somehow, an accustomed liar — the words roll easily off my tongue. Perhaps I am a traitor, I think, now that I dissemble as easily as one.\n" [Continue]
> "\"Go on,\" Harris says, giving me no indication of whether he believes my tale.\n" [Choices: "Assert" (0), "Imply" (1) -> 0]
> "\"I saw him take it,\" I continue. \"Collins was outside having a cigarette. Peterson was at the table. But I was at the front of the machine. I saw Hooper go around the side. He leant down and pulled something free. I even challenged him. I said, 'What's that? Someone put a nail somewhere they shouldn't have?' He didn't reply.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris watches me for a long moment.\n" [Continue]
> "\"We are left with two possibilities. You, or Hooper.\" The Commander pauses to smooth down his moustache. \"Hooper's in Hut 3 with the Captain, having a similar conversation.\"\n" [Choices: "\"And the other men?\"" (0), "\"Then you know I'm right.\"" (1) -> 0]
> "\"And the other men? Do we have a hut each? Are there  enough senior officers to go round?\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"Collins was outside when it happened, and Peterson can't get round the machine in that chair of his,\" Harris replies. \"That leaves you and Hooper. We're not in the business of guessing here at Bletchley. We are military intelligence. We get answers.\" Harris points a finger. \"And if that component has left these grounds, then every minute is critical.\"\n" [Choices: "Co-operate" (0), "Block" (1) -> 0]
> "\n" [Continue]
> "\"I'd be happy to help,\" I answer, leaning forwards. \"I'm sure there's something I could do.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"Like what, exactly?\"\n" [Choices: "\"Put me in with Hooper.\"" (0), "\"Tell Hooper I've confessed.\"" (1) -> 0]
