  step 53: text differs
    oracle: "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I saw him take it,\" I continue. \"Collins was outside having a cigarette. Peterson was at the table. But I was at the front of the machine. I saw Hooper go around the side. He leant down and pulled something free. I even challenged him. I said, 'What's that? Someone put a nail somewhere they shouldn't have?' He didn't reply.\"\n"
  step 54: text differs
    oracle: "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
    brink:  "Harris watches me for a long moment.\n"
  step 55: text differs
    oracle: "My plan now is to blame Hooper, but I cannot seem to tell the story. Whatever they put in my tea, it rules my tongue. I am desperate to tell him everything. I am weeping with shame.\n"
    brink:  "\"We are left with two possibilities. You, or Hooper.\" The Commander pauses to smooth down his moustache. \"Hooper's in Hut 3 with the Captain, having a similar conversation.\"\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Then you know I'm right. You knew all along. Why did you threaten me?\"\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
    brink:  "\"All we know is that we have a traitor, holding the fate of the country in his hands. We're not in the business of guessing here at Bletchley. We are military intelligence. We get answers.\" Harris points a finger. \"And if that component has left these grounds, then every minute is critical.\"\n"
  step 58: text differs
    oracle: "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"It's your problem. Your security breach. So much for your careful vetting process.\"\n"
  step 59: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "I lean back in my chair and fold my arms so the way they shake will not be visible.\n"
  step 60: text differs
    oracle: "\"No. Not for more than a moment, of course. Everyone here is marked out by how little we would be willing to say about it.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"You'd better get on with solving it, instead of wasting your time in here with me.\"\n"
  step 61: text differs
    oracle: "\"Only you told this young man more than a little, didn't you?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris harrumphs. He's thinking it all over.\n"
  step 62: missing (oracle: "I nod. \"He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n")
  step 63: missing (oracle: "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n")
  step 64: missing (oracle: "\n")
  step 65: missing (oracle: "\"It wasn't,\" I reply. \"But I doubt you'd understand.\"\n")
  step 66: missing (oracle: "He simply nods.\n")
  step 67: missing (oracle: "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n")
  step 68: missing (oracle: "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n")
  step 69: missing (oracle: "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n")
  step 70: missing (oracle: "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n")
  step 71: missing (oracle: "As Harris speaks I find myself suddenly sharply aware, as if waking from a long sleep. The table, the corrugated walls of the hut, everything seems suddenly more tangible than a moment before.\n")
  step 72: missing (oracle: "Whatever it was they put in my drink is wearing off.\n")

