    brink:  "\"No. Not for more than a moment, of course. Everyone here is marked out by how little we would be willing to say about it.\"\n"
  step 47: text differs
    oracle: "\"Smart man,\" he replies. \"You wouldn't last. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Only you told this young man more than a little, didn't you?\"\n"
  step 48: text differs
    oracle: "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
    brink:  "I nod. \"<>\n"
  step 49: text differs
    oracle: "My plan now is to blame Hooper, but I cannot seem to tell the story. Whatever they put in my tea, it rules my tongue. I am desperate to tell him everything. I am weeping with shame.\n"
    brink:  "He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
  step 50: text differs
    oracle: "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
    brink:  "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
  step 51: text differs
    oracle: "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
    brink:  "\"It's a lonely life in this place,\" I reply. \"Lonely - and still one never gets a moment to oneself.\"\n"
  step 52: text differs
    oracle: "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"That's how it is in the Service,\" Harris answers.\n"
  step 53: text differs
    oracle: "\"Yes, I considered it. He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I'm not in the Service.\"\n"
  step 54: text differs
    oracle: "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
    brink:  "Harris shakes his head. \"Yes, you are.\"\n"
  step 55: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "Then he waves the thought aside.\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "\"It wasn't,\" I reply. \"But I doubt you'd understand.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "He simply nods.\n"
    brink:  "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n"
  step 58: text differs
    oracle: "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n"
  step 59: text differs
    oracle: "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n"
    brink:  "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n"
  step 60: text differs
    oracle: "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 61: text differs
    oracle: "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"No, Harris. The young man wasn't blackmailing me.\" I take a deep breath. \"It was Hooper.\"\n"
  step 62: text differs
    oracle: "As Harris speaks I find myself suddenly sharply aware, as if waking from a long sleep. The table, the corrugated walls of the hut, everything seems suddenly more tangible than a moment before.\n"
    brink:  "\"Now look here,\" Harris interrupts. \"Don't start that again.\"\n"
  step 63: text differs
    oracle: "Whatever it was they put in my drink is wearing off.\n"
    brink:  "\"It's the truth, Harris. If I'm going to jail, so be it, but I won't hang at Traitor's Gate. Hooper was the one who told the boy about our work. Hooper put the boy on to me. I should have realised, of course. These things don't happen by chance. I was a fool to think they might. And then, once he had me compromised, he demanded I steal the part from the machine.\"\n"
  step 64: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"Which you did.\" Harris leans forward. \"And then what? You still have it? You've stashed it somewhere?\"\n"
  step 65: text differs
    oracle: "\"Yes. I suppose he was their agent. I should have realised but I didn't. Then he threatened to tell you. I thought you would have me locked up: I couldn't bear the thought of it. I love working here. I've never been so happy, so successful, anywhere before. I didn't want to lose it.\"\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 66: text differs
    oracle: "\"So what did you do with the component?\" Harris talks urgently. He grips his gloves tightly in one hand, perhaps prepared to lift them and strike if it is required. \"Have you passed it to this man already? Have you left it somewhere for him to find?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Yes. I only had a moment. -> reveal_location_of_component\n"

