> "\"It's a lonely life in this place,\" I reply. \"Lonely - and still one never gets a moment to oneself.\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"That's how it is in the Service,\" Harris answers.\n" [Choices: "Argue" (0), "Agree" (1) -> 1]
> "\"Perhaps. But I didn't choose this life.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris shakes his head. \"No. And there's plenty of others who didn't who are suffering far worse.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Then he waves the thought aside.\n" [Continue]
