> "Then he gets to his feet, and opens the door, and marches me out across the yard. The evening is drawing in and there's a chill in the air. My mind is racing. I have one opportunity here — a moment in which to put the fear of God into Hooper and make him do something foolish that places him in harm's way. But how to achieve it?\n" [Continue]
