    brink:  "\"Tell Hooper I've confessed. Better yet. Let him see you marching me off in handcuffs. Then let him go, and see what he does. Ten to one he'll go straight to wherever he's hidden that component and his game will be up.\"\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "\"Yes, I considered it. He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris nods slowly, chewing over the idea. It isn't a bad plan even — except, of course, Hooper has <i>not</i> hidden the component, and won't lead them anywhere. But that's a problem I might be able to solve once I'm out of this place; and once they're too busy dogging Hooper's steps from hut to hut.\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
    brink:  "\"Interesting,\" the Commander muses. \"But I'm not so sure he'd be that stupid. And if he's already passed the part on, the whole thing will only be a waste of time.\"\n"
  step 58: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"You're right. Let me talk to him, then. As a colleague. Maybe I can get something useful out of him.\"\n"
  step 59: text differs
    oracle: "\"It wasn't,\" I reply. \"But I doubt you'd understand.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris shakes his head.\n"
  step 60: text differs
    oracle: "He simply nods.\n"
    brink:  "\"He despises you. I don't see why he'd give himself up to you.\"\n"
  step 61: missing (oracle: "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n")
  step 62: missing (oracle: "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n")
  step 63: missing (oracle: "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n")
  step 64: missing (oracle: "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n")
  step 65: missing (oracle: "As Harris speaks I find myself suddenly sharply aware, as if waking from a long sleep. The table, the corrugated walls of the hut, everything seems suddenly more tangible than a moment before.\n")
  step 66: missing (oracle: "Whatever it was they put in my drink is wearing off.\n")
  step 67: missing (oracle: "\n")
  step 68: missing (oracle: "\"No, Harris. The young man wasn't blackmailing me.\" I take a deep breath. \"It was Hooper.\"\n")
  step 69: missing (oracle: "\"Hooper!\" Harris exclaims, in surprise. He does not doubt me for a moment.\n")
  step 70: missing (oracle: "\"It's the truth, Harris. If I'm going to jail, so be it, but I won't hang at Traitor's Gate. Hooper was the one who told the boy about our work. Hooper put the boy on to me. I should have realised, of course. These things don't happen by chance. I was a fool to think they might. And then, once he had me compromised, he demanded I steal the part from the machine.\"\n")
  step 71: missing (oracle: "\"Which you did.\" Harris leans forward. \"And then what? You still have it? You've stashed it somewhere?\"\n")

