    oracle: "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n"
    brink:  "\"I do.\"\n"
  step 29: text differs
    oracle: "\"So. Do you have it?\" Harris is wasting no time: Bletchley is his watch. \"Do you know where it is?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris stares back at me. He cannot have expected it to be so easy to break me.\n"
  step 30: text differs
    oracle: "\"I have no idea.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\"\n"
  step 31: text differs
    oracle: "There's an icy silence.\n"
    brink:  "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n"
  step 32: text differs
    oracle: "\"Now drink your tea and talk.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"You want to explain that?\"\n"
  step 33: text differs
    oracle: "I lift the cup to my lips and sip. He waits for me to swallow before speaking again.\n"
    brink:  "\"There's nothing to explain,\" I reply stiffly. \"I know where your component is because it's obvious where your component is. That doesn't mean I took it, just because I can figure out a simple problem, any more than it means I'm a German spy because I can crack their codes.\"\n"
  step 34: text differs
    oracle: "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he remarks, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Tell me, then,\" he asks. \"What's your theory? You're a smart fellow — as smart as they come around here, and that's saying something. What's your opinion on the missing component? Accident, perhaps? Or do you blame one of the other men? \"\n"
  step 36: text differs
    oracle: "\"I suppose so,\" I reply. \"I've done things I shouldn't have done.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"An accident, naturally.\" I risk a smile. \"That damned machine is made from spare parts and string. Even these Huts leak when it rains. It wouldn't take more than one fellow to trip over a cable to shake out a component. Have you tried looking under the thing?\"\n"
  step 37: text differs
    oracle: "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Do you believe we haven't?\"\n"
  step 38: text differs
    oracle: "\"That's it,\" I reply. \"There are some things... which a man shouldn't do.\"\n"
    brink:  "In a sudden moment I understand that his reply is a threat.\n"
  step 39: text differs
    oracle: "Harris doesn't stiffen. Doesn't lean away, as though my condition might be infectious. I had thought they trained them in the army to shoot my kind on sight.\n"
    brink:  "\"Now,\" he continues. \"Are you sure there isn't anything you want to tell me?\"\n"
  step 40: text differs
    oracle: "He offers no sympathy either. He nods, once. His understanding of me is a mere turning cog in his calculations, with no meaning to it.\n"
    brink:  "\"All right.\" With a sigh, your defiance collapses. \"If you're searched my things then I suppose you've found my letters. Haven't you? In fact, if you haven't, don't tell me.\n"
  step 41: text differs
    oracle: "\"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris nods once. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
  step 43: outcome differs
    oracle: Choices { choices: OracleChoicesData { presented: [OracleChoiceRecord { text: "Agree", index: 0, tags: [] }, OracleChoiceRecord { text: "Disagree", index: 1, tags: [] }, OracleChoiceRecord { text: "Apologise", index: 2, tags: [] }], selected: 1 } }
    brink:  Choices { presented: [ChoiceRecord { text: "Agree", index: 0, tags: [] }, ChoiceRecord { text: "Disagree", index: 1, tags: [] }, ChoiceRecord { text: "Lie", index: 2, tags: [] }], selected: 0 }
  step 45: text differs
    oracle: "\"I can still fix this.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"What could I do?\" I'm shaking now. The night is cold and the heat—lamp in the Hut has been removed. \"I don't want to go to prison.\"\n"
  step 46: text differs
    oracle: "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Smart man,\" he replies. \"You wouldn't last.  So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
  step 48: text differs
    oracle: "My plan now is to blame Hooper, but I cannot seem to tell the story. Whatever they put in my tea, it rules my tongue. I am desperate to tell him everything. I am weeping with shame.\n"
    brink:  "\"I saw Hooper take it.\"\n"
  step 49: text differs
    oracle: "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\" He is starting to lose his patience. I have seen Harris angry a few times, with lackeys and secretaries. But never with us. With the 'brains' he has always been cautious, treating us like children.\n"
  step 50: text differs
    oracle: "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
    brink:  "And now I see that, like a father, he wants to smack us when we disobey him.\n"
  step 51: text differs
    oracle: "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Just get to the truth, man. Every <i>minute</i> matters.\"\n"
  step 52: text differs
    oracle: "\"Yes, I considered it. He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 53: text differs
    oracle: "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
    brink:  "\"Very well. I see there's no point in covering up. You know everything anyway.\"\n"
  step 54: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "Harris nods, and waits for me to continue.\n"
  step 55: text differs
    oracle: "\"It wasn't,\" I reply. \"But I doubt you'd understand.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "He simply nods.\n"
    brink:  "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
  step 58: text differs
    oracle: "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n"
    brink:  "\"Yes, I considered it. <>\n"
  step 59: text differs
    oracle: "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n"
    brink:  "He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
  step 60: text differs
    oracle: "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n"
    brink:  "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
  step 61: text differs
    oracle: "As Harris speaks I find myself suddenly sharply aware, as if waking from a long sleep. The table, the corrugated walls of the hut, everything seems suddenly more tangible than a moment before.\n"
    brink:  "\"The boy was a pretty simpleton. Quite inferior. His good opinion meant nothing to be. Harris, do not misunderstand. I was simply after his body.\"\n"
  step 62: text differs
    oracle: "Whatever it was they put in my drink is wearing off.\n"
    brink:  "Harris, to his credit, doesn't flinch; but I can see he will have nightmares of this moment later tonight. I'm tempted to reach out and take his hand to worsen it for him.\n"
  step 63: extra ("\"Go on with your confession.\"\n")
  step 64: extra ("\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n")
  step 65: extra ("\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n")

