  step 23: text differs
    oracle: "\"Awkward,\" I reply, sipping at my tea as though we were old friends.\n"
    brink:  "\"Awkward,\" I reply\n"
  step 24: text differs
    oracle: "His face is telling me nothing. I've seen Harris broad and full of laughter. Today he is tight, as much part of the military machine as the device in Hut 5.\n"
    brink:  "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n"
  step 25: text differs
    oracle: "\"We need that component,\" he says.\n"
    brink:  "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n"
  step 26: text differs
    oracle: "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n"
    brink:  "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n"
  step 27: text differs
    oracle: "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n"
    brink:  "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he replies, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n"
  step 28: text differs
    oracle: "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n"
    brink:  "\"I do.\"\n"
  step 29: text differs
    oracle: "\"So. Do you have it?\" Harris is wasting no time: Bletchley is his watch. \"Do you know where it is?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris stares back at me. He cannot have expected it to be so easy to break me.\n"
  step 30: text differs
    oracle: "\"I do.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\"\n"
  step 31: text differs
    oracle: "Harris smiles with satisfaction, as if your willingness to talk was somehow his doing.\n"
    brink:  "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n"
  step 32: text differs
    oracle: "\"I see.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"You want to explain that?\"\n"
  step 33: text differs
    oracle: "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 34: text differs
    oracle: "\"You want to explain that?\"\n"
    brink:  "I pause a moment, trying to choose my words. To just come out and say it, after a lifetime of hiding... that is a circle I cannot square.\n"
  step 35: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"I've done things,\" I begin. \"Things I didn't want to do. I tried not to. But in the end, it felt like cutting off my own arm to resist.\"\n"
  step 36: text differs
    oracle: "I pause a moment, trying to choose my words. To just come out and say it, after a lifetime of hiding... that is a circle I cannot square.\n"
    brink:  "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n"
  step 37: text differs
    oracle: "\"I've done things,\" I begin. \"Things I didn't want to do. I tried not to. But in the end, it felt like cutting off my own arm to resist.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"That's it,\" I reply. \"There are some things... which a man shouldn't do.\"\n"
  step 38: text differs
    oracle: "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris doesn't stiffen. Doesn't lean away, as though my condition might be infectious. I had thought they trained them in the army to shoot my kind on sight.\n"
  step 39: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "He offers no sympathy either. He nods, once. His understanding of me is a mere turning cog in his calculations, with no meaning to it.\n"
  step 40: text differs
    oracle: "I shake my head violently, to say no, that's not it, but whatever is wrong with tongue is wrong with neck too. I look across at the table at Harris' face and realise with a start how sympathetic he is. Such a kind, generous man. How can I hold anything back from him?\n"
    brink:  "\"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
  step 41: text differs
    oracle: "I take another mouthful of the bitter, strange—tasting tea before answering.\n"
    brink:  "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n"
  step 42: text differs
    oracle: "\"That's it,\" I reply. \"There are some things... which a man shouldn't do.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Now they own you.\"\n"
  step 43: text differs
    oracle: "Harris doesn't stiffen. Doesn't lean away, as though my condition might be infectious. I had thought they trained them in the army to shoot my kind on sight.\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 44: text differs
    oracle: "He offers no sympathy either. He nods, once. His understanding of me is a mere turning cog in his calculations, with no meaning to it.\n"
    brink:  "\"I can still fix this.\"\n"
  step 45: text differs
    oracle: "\"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
  step 46: text differs
    oracle: "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n"
    brink:  "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
  step 47: text differs
    oracle: "\"Now they own you.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I saw Hooper take it.\"\n"
  step 48: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\" He is starting to lose his patience. I have seen Harris angry a few times, with lackeys and secretaries. But never with us. With the 'brains' he has always been cautious, treating us like children.\n"
  step 49: text differs
    oracle: "\"I can still fix this.\"\n"
    brink:  "And now I see that, like a father, he wants to smack us when we disobey him.\n"
  step 50: text differs
    oracle: "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Just get to the truth, man. Every <i>minute</i> matters.\"\n"
  step 51: text differs
    oracle: "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 52: text differs
    oracle: "My plan now is to blame Hooper, but I cannot seem to tell the story. Whatever they put in my tea, it rules my tongue. I am desperate to tell him everything. I am weeping with shame.\n"
    brink:  "\"Very well. I see there's no point in covering up. You know everything anyway.\"\n"
  step 53: text differs
    oracle: "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris nods, and waits for me to continue.\n"
  step 54: text differs
    oracle: "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
    brink:  "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
  step 55: text differs
    oracle: "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "\"No. Not for more than a moment, of course. Everyone here is marked out by how little we would be willing to say about it.\"\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 58: text differs
