> "\"Go on,\" Harris says, giving me no indication of whether he believes my tale.\n" [Choices: "Assert" (0), "Imply" (1) -> 0]
> "\"I saw him take it,\" I continue. \"Collins was outside having a cigarette. Peterson was at the table. But I was at the front of the machine. I saw Hooper go around the side. He leant down and pulled something free. I even challenged him. I said, 'What's that? Someone put a nail somewhere they shouldn't have?' He didn't reply.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris watches me for a long moment.\n" [Continue]
> "\"We are left with two possibilities. You, or Hooper.\" The Commander pauses to smooth down his moustache. \"Hooper's in Hut 3 with the Captain, having a similar conversation.\"\n" [Choices: "\"And the other men?\"" (0), "\"Then you know I'm right.\"" (1) -> 0]
> "\"And the other men? Do we have a hut each? Are there  enough senior officers to go round?\"\n" [Continue]
> "\"Collins was outside when it happened, and Peterson can't get round the machine in that chair of his,\" Harris replies. \"That leaves you and Hooper. We're not in the business of guessing here at Bletchley. We are military intelligence. We get answers.\" Harris points a finger. \"And if that component has left these grounds, then every minute is critical.\"\n" [Choices: "Co-operate" (0), "Block" (1) -> 1]
> "\"It's your problem. Your security breach. So much for your careful vetting process.\"\n" [Continue]
> "I lean back in my chair and fold my arms so the way they shake will not be visible.\n" [Continue]
> "\"You'd better get on with solving it, instead of wasting your time in here with me.\"\n" [Continue]
> "Harris harrumphs. He's thinking it all over.\n" [Done]
outcome: Done
  step 23: text differs
    oracle: "\"Awkward,\" I reply, sipping at my tea as though we were old friends.\n"
    brink:  "\"Awkward,\" I reply\n"
  step 24: text differs
    oracle: "His face is telling me nothing. I've seen Harris broad and full of laughter. Today he is tight, as much part of the military machine as the device in Hut 5.\n"
    brink:  "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n"
  step 25: text differs
    oracle: "\"We need that component,\" he says.\n"
    brink:  "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n"
  step 26: text differs
    oracle: "The reel went missing from the Bombe this afternoon. The four of us were in the Hut, working on the latest German intercept. The results were garbage. It was Russell who found the gap in the plugboard.\n"
    brink:  "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n"
  step 27: text differs
    oracle: "Any of us could have taken it; and no one else would have known its worth.\n"
    brink:  "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he replies, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n"
  step 28: text differs
    oracle: "They will pin it on me. They need a scapegoat so that the work can continue. I'm a likely target. Weaker than the rest.\n"
    brink:  "\"I do.\"\n"
  step 29: text differs
    oracle: "\"So. Do you have it?\" Harris is wasting no time: Bletchley is his watch. \"Do you know where it is?\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris stares back at me. He cannot have expected it to be so easy to break me.\n"
  step 30: text differs
    oracle: "\"I have no idea.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\"\n"
  step 31: text differs
    oracle: "There's an icy silence.\n"
    brink:  "There's a long pause, like the delay between feeding a line of cypher into the Bombe and waiting for its valves to warm up enough to begin processing.\n"
  step 32: text differs
    oracle: "\"Now drink your tea and talk.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"You want to explain that?\"\n"
  step 33: text differs
    oracle: "I lift the cup to my lips and sip. He waits for me to swallow before speaking again.\n"
    brink:  "\"There's nothing to explain,\" I reply stiffly. \"I know where your component is because it's obvious where your component is. That doesn't mean I took it, just because I can figure out a simple problem, any more than it means I'm a German spy because I can crack their codes.\"\n"
  step 34: text differs
    oracle: "\"Lapsang Souchong,\" he remarks, placing his own cup back on the table untouched. \"Such a curious flavour. It might almost not be tea at all. You might say it hides a multitude of sins. As do you. Isn't that right?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Tell me, then,\" he asks. \"What's your theory? You're a smart fellow — as smart as they come around here, and that's saying something. What's your opinion on the missing component? Accident, perhaps? Or do you blame one of the other men? \"\n"
  step 36: text differs
    oracle: "\"I suppose so,\" I reply. \"I've done things I shouldn't have done.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"An accident, naturally.\" I risk a smile. \"That damned machine is made from spare parts and string. Even these Huts leak when it rains. It wouldn't take more than one fellow to trip over a cable to shake out a component. Have you tried looking under the thing?\"\n"
  step 37: text differs
    oracle: "\"You mean you've left yourself open,\" Harris answers. \"To pressure. Is that what you're saying?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Do you believe we haven't?\"\n"
  step 38: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "In a sudden moment I understand that his reply is a threat.\n"
  step 39: text differs
    oracle: "\"We're all under pressure here.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"Now,\" he continues. \"Are you sure there isn't anything you want to tell me?\"\n"
  step 40: text differs
    oracle: "He looks at me with pity. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"All right.\" With a sigh, your defiance collapses. \"If you're searched my things then I suppose you've found my letters. Haven't you? In fact, if you haven't, don't tell me.\n"
  step 41: text differs
    oracle: "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n"
    brink:  "Harris nods once. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
  step 42: text differs
    oracle: "\"Now they own you.\"\n"
    brink:  "He slides his thumb between two fingers.\n"
  step 43: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"Now they own you.\"\n"
  step 44: text differs
    oracle: "\"I can still fix this.\"\n"
    brink:  "\n"
  step 45: text differs
    oracle: "Harris shakes his head. \"You'll do nothing. This is beyond you now. You may go to prison or may go to firing squad - or we can change your name and move you somewhere where your indiscretions can't hurt you. But right now, none of that matters. What happens to you doesn't matter. All that matters is where that component is. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I wanted to tell you,\" I tell him. \"I thought I could find out who they were. Lead you to them.\"\n"
  step 46: text differs
    oracle: "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
    brink:  "Harris looks at me with contempt. \"You wretch. You'll pay for what you've done to this country today. If a single man loses his life because of your pride and your perversions then God help your soul. So why don't you tell me, right now. Where is it?\"\n"
  step 47: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "His eyes bear down like carbonised drill—bits.\n"
  step 48: text differs
    oracle: "\"All right. I'll tell you what happened.\" And never mind my shame.\n"
    brink:  "\"I saw Hooper take it.\"\n"
  step 49: text differs
    oracle: "\"I can imagine how it starts,\" he replies.\n"
    brink:  "\"I see.\" He is starting to lose his patience. I have seen Harris angry a few times, with lackeys and secretaries. But never with us. With the 'brains' he has always been cautious, treating us like children.\n"
  step 50: text differs
    oracle: "\"There was a young man. I met him in the town. A few months ago now. We got to talking. Not about work. And I used my cover story, but he seemed to know it wasn't true. That got me wondering if he might be one of us.\"\n"
    brink:  "And now I see that, like a father, he wants to smack us when we disobey him.\n"
  step 51: text differs
    oracle: "Harris is not letting me off any more.\n"
    brink:  "\"Just get to the truth, man. Every <i>minute</i> matters.\"\n"
  step 52: text differs
    oracle: "\"You seriously entertained that possibility?\"\n"
    brink:  "\"I know what you're thinking. If I've transgressed once then I must be guilty of everything else... But I'm not. We were close to cracking the 13th's intercept. We were getting correlations in the data. Then Hooper disappeared for a moment, and next minute the machine was down.\"\n"
  step 53: text differs
    oracle: "\"Yes, I considered it. He seemed to know all about me. He... he was quite enchanted by my achievements.\"\n"
    brink:  "I have become, somehow, an accustomed liar — the words roll easily off my tongue. Perhaps I am a traitor, I think, now that I dissemble as easily as one.\n"
  step 54: text differs
    oracle: "The way Harris is staring I expect him to strike me, but he does not. He replies, \"I can see how that must have been attractive to you,\" with such plain—spokeness that I think I must have misheard.\n"
    brink:  "\"Go on,\" Harris says, giving me no indication of whether he believes my tale.\n"
  step 55: text differs
    oracle: "\n"
    brink:  "\"I saw him take it,\" I continue. \"Collins was outside having a cigarette. Peterson was at the table. But I was at the front of the machine. I saw Hooper go around the side. He leant down and pulled something free. I even challenged him. I said, 'What's that? Someone put a nail somewhere they shouldn't have?' He didn't reply.\"\n"
  step 56: text differs
    oracle: "\"It wasn't,\" I reply. \"But I doubt you'd understand.\"\n"
    brink:  "Harris watches me for a long moment.\n"
  step 57: text differs
    oracle: "He simply nods.\n"
    brink:  "\"We are left with two possibilities. You, or Hooper.\" The Commander pauses to smooth down his moustache. \"Hooper's in Hut 3 with the Captain, having a similar conversation.\"\n"
  step 58: text differs
    oracle: "\"Go on with your confession.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"And the other men? Do we have a hut each? Are there  enough senior officers to go round?\"\n"
  step 59: text differs
    oracle: "That gives me pause. I hadn't thought of it as such. But I suppose he's right. I am about to admit what I did.\n"
    brink:  "\"Collins was outside when it happened, and Peterson can't get round the machine in that chair of his,\" Harris replies. \"That leaves you and Hooper. We're not in the business of guessing here at Bletchley. We are military intelligence. We get answers.\" Harris points a finger. \"And if that component has left these grounds, then every minute is critical.\"\n"
  step 60: text differs
    oracle: "\"There's not much else to say. I took the part from Bombe computing device. You seem to know that already. I had to. He was going to expose me if I didn't.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"It's your problem. Your security breach. So much for your careful vetting process.\"\n"
  step 61: text differs
    oracle: "\"This young man was blackmailing you over your affair?\"\n"
    brink:  "I lean back in my chair and fold my arms so the way they shake will not be visible.\n"
  step 62: text differs
    oracle: "As Harris speaks I find myself suddenly sharply aware, as if waking from a long sleep. The table, the corrugated walls of the hut, everything seems suddenly more tangible than a moment before.\n"
    brink:  "\"You'd better get on with solving it, instead of wasting your time in here with me.\"\n"
  step 63: text differs
    oracle: "Whatever it was they put in my drink is wearing off.\n"
    brink:  "Harris harrumphs. He's thinking it all over.\n"

